  </title>
  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">DRC will implement an integrated, protection-centered emergency intervention through rapid  basic  needs  and  protection  while  transitioning  the  most  vulnerable  to  economic recovery assistance. 

The cost extension granted by FCDO will allow DRC to scale-up certain activities  (EORE,  Shelter,  IPA,  Protection  Kits,  CfW),  introduce  a  new  intervention (protection  information  sessions),  and  continue  to  monitor  and  coach  business  grant beneficiaries who were assisted during the first quarter of 2022</narrative>
